Articles.Content:
Hello, I have a strange issue: game crashing on launch and I don't see something in game logs.

I have clean game without mods installed via steam. If I just run game - it crashes on load. If I run game and switch to other task - the game will load at background, but will crash in menu if I try to enter options, credits or anything else. Windowed and fullscreen - same result. I tried to delete all game files and download it again or check game files - same result, still crashing.

42 minutes ago, Skauber said:

There must be some bad interaction between MSI Afterburner and either Unity or specifically KSP.

It's not MSI Afterburner itself, it's the RivaTuner Statistics Server component that it uses to display overlays.
Anything that displays overlays in-game is probably doing so by hijacking the rendering path - this has been known to crash several games, KSP included.

This has been known for a long time, but I don't see it in the tech support stickies...

Yep, seems that is correct. I completely disabled RivaTuner, never used it anyway, and KSP works fine with Afterburner running. I haven't had any issues with other games so far, so I guess I've been lucky. Since I don't use RivaTuner it's a non-issue for me, now that I know the solution.
